WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:03.003
[dog barking]

00:03.003 --> 00:06.006
[footsteps thudding]
[people grunting, panting]

00:07.257 --> 00:08.258
GIRL:
Careful.

00:09.259 --> 00:10.260
BOY:
You're drunk.

00:13.013 --> 00:14.348
[indistinct talking]

00:16.558 --> 00:18.310
BOY:
Okay, here's good.

00:18.310 --> 00:19.186
[thuds]

00:19.186 --> 00:20.103
[girl giggling]

00:20.103 --> 00:22.064
Let's get out of here.
GIRL: Okay. Go, go. Come on.

00:22.064 --> 00:23.190
[both giggling]

00:25.275 --> 00:27.027
[retches and vomits]

00:28.445 --> 00:29.446
[Rae groaning]

00:39.623 --> 00:41.124
Is that the Little Dipper?

00:42.167 --> 00:44.044
That's the Big Dipper, doofus.

00:44.044 --> 00:46.964
Actually, you're both wrong.

00:46.964 --> 00:48.048
LITTLE CLARE:
Can we go back now?

00:48.048 --> 00:49.049
FRANKIE:
Nope.

00:49.675 --> 00:51.718
Be patient, sweet peas.

00:51.718 --> 00:54.137
YOUNG CLARE:
I'm tired. It's too hot.

00:54.137 --> 00:55.806
You said you wanted air.

00:55.806 --> 00:58.725
Conditioning. I want air-conditioning.

00:58.725 --> 01:00.853
Well, we would need
electricity for that.

01:01.562 --> 01:03.230
And a bathroom inside.

01:03.647 --> 01:05.941
Everyone I know gets to poop inside.

01:07.401 --> 01:09.611
And you will have
all those things someday.

01:10.320 --> 01:13.699
But this...
This is better than any of those things.

01:14.825 --> 01:15.826
I promise.

01:15.826 --> 01:17.452
[gate squeaking]

01:18.453 --> 01:20.372
[whispering] Okay. It's time.

01:21.081 --> 01:22.541
Close your eyes.

01:23.458 --> 01:25.252
And be really quiet.

01:25.878 --> 01:27.629
And I'll say when you can open them.

01:27.629 --> 01:29.298
- [horse nickers]
- What's that noise?

01:34.553 --> 01:36.555
[horses nickering]

01:40.434 --> 01:42.269
[whispering] Okay. Now.

01:44.938 --> 01:46.273
[horse whinnying]
[Little Clare gasps]

01:46.773 --> 01:49.776
♪

02:03.123 --> 02:06.126
♪

02:23.310 --> 02:25.270
LITTLE LUCAS:
Do they belong to us, Mommy?

02:25.270 --> 02:26.939
I wish they did.

02:28.023 --> 02:29.149
Hi, Lady.

02:29.942 --> 02:31.777
You sweet, sweet girl.

02:51.213 --> 02:52.631
What the fuck?

02:53.340 --> 02:54.341
[phone chimes]

02:57.636 --> 02:59.638
"Due to your pending investigation,

02:59.638 --> 03:02.975
you are required to complete
an online ethics and boundaries course."

03:02.975 --> 03:04.601
Oh, fuck you, boundaries.

03:06.270 --> 03:07.479
[phone chimes]

03:11.775 --> 03:12.985
Mm.

03:12.985 --> 03:13.986
[door opens]

03:13.986 --> 03:16.029
DANNY:
Clare! Clare, come here!

03:19.658 --> 03:20.701
Why is she on a surfboard?

03:20.701 --> 03:22.119
I don't know.
I just came outside and she was--

03:22.119 --> 03:24.246
CLARE:
Rae, are you okay? Are you hurt?

03:24.246 --> 03:26.039
What-- Uh-- What-- Uh, who left you here?

03:26.039 --> 03:29.001
No one. I'm f-- I'm fine.

03:31.920 --> 03:33.505
Frankie Rae, are you drunk?

03:33.505 --> 03:35.465
Have you guys ever had a White Russian?

03:35.465 --> 03:37.426
Since when do you drink, Rae?
CLARE: Oh, my God.

03:37.426 --> 03:39.845
Rae, I need you to get up right now
and come inside the house.

03:40.345 --> 03:41.930
[Rae mumbles]

03:41.930 --> 03:44.850
Frankie Rae, I want you
to look at me and talk to me right now.

03:45.475 --> 03:47.436
Who left you here like this?

03:47.436 --> 03:50.189
Was it those awful threesome people?
Is that who did this?

03:50.189 --> 03:51.023
Are they the same ones

03:51.023 --> 03:52.858
- who made you eat that cucumber?
- What?

03:52.858 --> 03:53.775
CLARE:
I saw that.

03:53.775 --> 03:55.444
Did they make you eat that cucumber?

03:55.444 --> 03:56.653
Who made you eat that cucumber?

03:58.614 --> 04:00.824
MAN: [on video]
<i>I love what you did
with the Peterson case.</i>

04:00.824 --> 04:03.869
<i>You know, a massage
can make a stressful day seem better.</i>

04:03.869 --> 04:06.914
WOMAN: [on video] <i>That sounds great,
but I actually have to get home.</i>

04:08.415 --> 04:12.044
<i>So we see here that Bob
is not only being suggestive to Rhonda,</i>

04:12.044 --> 04:13.921
<i>he's violating her personal space.</i>

04:13.921 --> 04:16.381
<i>And that's the thing
about personal space.</i>

04:16.381 --> 04:17.591
It's personal.

04:21.220 --> 04:22.221
[quick knocks on door]

04:22.221 --> 04:23.639
All right, come on. Let's wake up.

04:26.308 --> 04:27.309
Now!

04:27.309 --> 04:28.310
We're gonna be--

04:29.770 --> 04:31.897
Now! Let's get up. Let's go!

04:37.069 --> 04:38.237
RAE:
I hate those stars.

04:38.237 --> 04:41.198
What?
You named your first hamster Cassiopeia.

04:41.198 --> 04:43.116
Yeah, well, I'm taking them down.

04:43.116 --> 04:44.660
Your dad is playing today.

04:44.660 --> 04:45.827
You need to be there early.

04:45.827 --> 04:49.623
And having a hangover does not qualify
as a reason to skip church.

04:49.623 --> 04:51.875
RAE: Why do you even care?
You don't even believe in God.

04:51.875 --> 04:55.462
It's Easter,
and it is time to <i>resurrect.</i>

04:57.089 --> 04:58.465
[Rae groans]
Let's go.

05:00.259 --> 05:01.260
[Rae sighs]

05:03.470 --> 05:04.930
You skip every Sunday.

05:04.930 --> 05:06.431
Su-- Sundays are my time to write.

05:06.431 --> 05:07.808
RAE:
Yeah, except you never do.

05:09.726 --> 05:11.937
Do you realize that
you could've been assaulted last night?

05:12.604 --> 05:13.605
Or worse.

05:14.731 --> 05:18.610
And your so-called <i>friends</i>
just left you on our lawn

05:18.610 --> 05:20.529
to choke on your own barf.

05:20.529 --> 05:21.947
So who was that? Was that Montana?

05:21.947 --> 05:23.073
It wasn't Montana.

05:23.073 --> 05:25.492
Wh-- Wh-- Why can't you
make some just nice new friends?

05:25.492 --> 05:28.120
- Like, what happened to Bethany from dance?
- Can you just stop?

05:28.120 --> 05:29.955
Do you know
if something happened to you,

05:29.955 --> 05:31.707
I would not be able to survive?

05:31.707 --> 05:33.709
Do you realize that? I would die!

05:33.709 --> 05:35.085
My life would be over!

05:35.085 --> 05:36.628
I would not be able to go on.

05:36.628 --> 05:38.172
Then I guess you shouldn't have had me!

05:40.757 --> 05:41.758
[door closes]

05:43.552 --> 05:45.762
Why are you mad at me?

05:46.555 --> 05:47.556
Frankie?

05:48.223 --> 05:49.141
Frankie?

05:49.141 --> 05:50.517
Stop calling me that!

05:50.517 --> 05:52.728
When is this bullshit gonna end?

05:52.728 --> 05:54.855
The White Russians, and the surfboards,

05:54.855 --> 05:59.318
and the giving a shit about a person
that is so clearly beneath you?

05:59.318 --> 06:01.653
And rejecting your own grandmother's name?

06:01.653 --> 06:03.822
She was <i>never</i> my grandmother!

06:03.822 --> 06:04.823
[door slams shut]

06:05.824 --> 06:06.825
[exhales]

06:07.993 --> 06:08.994
[groans]

06:11.997 --> 06:14.124
Well, can you talk to her?
Because she fucking hates me.

06:14.124 --> 06:16.335
Yeah, yeah.
I'm gonna do a lot more than talk to her.

06:16.919 --> 06:18.170
I'm gonna ground her ass.

06:19.004 --> 06:20.714
Really? An Easter basket?

06:20.714 --> 06:22.341
Well, it's tradition.

06:23.800 --> 06:24.760
Tradition as well?

06:27.012 --> 06:28.013
Oh, my God.

06:28.013 --> 06:29.765
Was that pickle flavored?

06:38.273 --> 06:39.441
Happy Easter.

06:40.359 --> 06:41.693
Let's go.

06:53.330 --> 06:55.207
So I'll just meet you at brunch then?

06:55.207 --> 06:56.834
Oh, so you're coming to brunch?

06:56.834 --> 06:58.293
Unless it's going to feel weird.

06:58.836 --> 06:59.920
I mean, why wouldn't I--

06:59.920 --> 07:02.840
No, no. I mean, it won't be weird
if we don't make it weird.

07:02.840 --> 07:04.925
I just don't want
anyone to think anything is wrong.

07:08.178 --> 07:09.471
Okay, um...

07:09.471 --> 07:10.931
If you don't want to go, then don't go.

07:10.931 --> 07:12.975
I'll just make an excuse then, you know?

07:12.975 --> 07:15.936
Uh, you can stay here.
I'll tell them that you're--

07:15.936 --> 07:16.937
that you're writing.

07:16.937 --> 07:19.231
That wouldn't be an excuse. I do write.

07:19.231 --> 07:21.483
I'll take this
just in case she changes her mind.

07:21.483 --> 07:23.443
Danny,
I haven't even said that I'm not gonna--

07:23.443 --> 07:25.863
I-- I'm coming. I can bring the basket.

07:25.863 --> 07:27.531
Look, I, uh, I think you're right.

07:27.531 --> 07:30.576
You know, we don't want 'em
to know that things aren't normal.

07:30.576 --> 07:31.743
Happy writing.

07:35.747 --> 07:36.748
[door closes]

07:40.169 --> 07:43.172
♪

07:59.563 --> 08:01.565
[telephone ringing]

08:05.736 --> 08:07.446
Hello?
FRANKIE: [over phone] <i>Hi, honey.</i>

08:07.446 --> 08:09.990
Hi. Hey, Mom.
Um, sorry, can I call you back?

08:09.990 --> 08:13.202
I'm working on
that essay competition for <i>Pleiades.</i>

08:13.202 --> 08:14.286
I need you to come home.

08:15.120 --> 08:16.371
Why? What's wrong?

08:16.371 --> 08:17.122
Today.

08:17.122 --> 08:18.415
CLARE: [over phone]
<i>Today? No, I can't, Mom.</i>

08:18.415 --> 08:20.083
<i>I have work, then class tonight.</i>

08:20.083 --> 08:21.293
You need to come home right now.

08:24.588 --> 08:25.589
Okay.

08:27.758 --> 08:28.759
Okay. Yeah.

08:30.093 --> 08:31.094
Sure.

08:33.972 --> 08:34.973
WOMAN:
<i>Dear Sugar,</i>

08:35.599 --> 08:40.270
<i>I'm writing this from my little bed
in the Pediatric Intensive Care Unit.</i>

08:41.104 --> 08:43.023
<i>My husband and I just found out</i>

08:43.023 --> 08:47.486
<i>that our six-month-old daughter
has a brain tumor</i>

08:47.486 --> 08:50.614
<i>and she's having brain surgery tomorrow.</i>

08:53.116 --> 08:55.744
<i>People have poured
all their thoughts and prayers</i>

08:55.744 --> 08:56.954
<i>into us right now.</i>

09:04.211 --> 09:06.547
<i>I want to believe the prayers are working,</i>

09:06.547 --> 09:08.507
<i>but... I don't know.</i>

09:11.218 --> 09:13.303
<i>I've never been super religious</i>

09:14.972 --> 09:19.977
<i>but... now I find myself
doubting God's existence</i>

09:20.769 --> 09:21.770
<i>more than ever.</i>

09:25.190 --> 09:29.987
<i>I'm so scared
that I'll lose my sweet baby girl.</i>

09:31.113 --> 09:32.489
<i>If there was a God,</i>

09:33.991 --> 09:35.993
<i>why would He let this happen to us?</i>

09:41.039 --> 09:43.584
[phone vibrating]

09:49.339 --> 09:50.549
AMY:
Well, at least she made it home.

09:51.633 --> 09:55.888
How many shit bunkers
did we happen to wake up in?

09:56.847 --> 09:58.432
Remember Burger?
CLARE: Oh, God.

09:58.432 --> 09:59.391
With the van?

09:59.975 --> 10:02.352
And the trash bag
that was full of mushrooms?

10:02.352 --> 10:05.063
What? What?
[Clare laughing]

10:05.063 --> 10:08.442
Do you remember that he would
just play <i>Free Bird</i> on repeat?

10:09.401 --> 10:11.528
And also, P.S. <i>vans.</i>

10:11.528 --> 10:13.071
Vans.
CLARE: Terrifying!

10:13.071 --> 10:15.199
Vans. Ugh.

10:15.199 --> 10:17.492
It's kind of a miracle
that we're alive, really.

10:17.492 --> 10:18.577
- When you think about it.
- Yep.

10:19.244 --> 10:21.288
Hi. Can you just keep these coming?

10:21.288 --> 10:22.289
WAITER: Sure.
AMY: Thank you.

10:23.874 --> 10:27.044
Wow. Come on, Frankie,
well, she's a good girl.

10:27.044 --> 10:30.130
Rae!
AMY: Whatever she would like to be called.

10:30.130 --> 10:32.049
She's-- She's way smarter
than we ever were.

10:33.258 --> 10:34.259
Okay?

10:34.885 --> 10:38.013
Oh, she has to be careful. She does.

10:38.013 --> 10:39.139
I got something.

10:39.556 --> 10:42.434
You'll think I'm brilliant.
Here, take these.

10:42.434 --> 10:43.644
Is that a-- What is that?

10:43.644 --> 10:45.020
Those are fentanyl strips.

10:45.020 --> 10:48.023
And they're like the free condoms now.

10:48.023 --> 10:50.234
I keep 'em at the bar.
Uh, just give 'em to her.

10:50.234 --> 10:52.152
She can test <i>everything</i> that she's taking.

10:52.152 --> 10:54.279
I know. You wouldn't really think it,

10:54.279 --> 10:56.573
but that shit is just <i>everywhere.</i>

10:56.573 --> 10:58.242
Are you kidding me?
AMY: No.

10:58.242 --> 11:00.661
Now I have to worry about fentanyl
on top of everything else?

11:00.661 --> 11:01.662
AMY:
Yeah, you do.

11:02.204 --> 11:04.831
WOMAN: Good Bloody Mary?
[baby crying]

11:07.835 --> 11:09.086
Thanks for the help, Sugar.

11:12.089 --> 11:13.549
AMY: [from distance]

11:14.675 --> 11:15.676
Are you okay?

11:16.134 --> 11:17.135
Yo!

11:17.135 --> 11:19.930
Oh, God. Spin-city.

11:21.640 --> 11:23.016
I mean, it's basically like...

11:23.016 --> 11:24.017
Um...

11:25.769 --> 11:26.770
Are you okay?

11:26.770 --> 11:28.230
CLARE:
I-- I--

11:28.230 --> 11:30.607
I'm sorry. I have to go.
AMY: You gotta go?

11:30.607 --> 11:31.900
- We haven't gotten...
- I know.

11:31.900 --> 11:33.902
...to the bottom
of our bottomless, please.

11:33.902 --> 11:37.948
Listen, I'm gonna Venmo you
for all of this. It's on me.

11:37.948 --> 11:39.157
AMY:
What are you doing?

11:40.784 --> 11:41.785
Love you.

11:41.785 --> 11:44.496
- If it's the fentanyl strips, I'm sorry.
- No, it's not the fentanyl strips.

11:44.496 --> 11:46.248
- I love you.
- I'm sorry-- No, 'cause you're spinning.

11:46.248 --> 11:48.000
I'm not spinning. I love you.
AMY: You are.

11:50.127 --> 11:51.128
YOUNG CLARE:
Hi, Mom.

11:51.670 --> 11:53.422
Thanks for coming, sweet pea.

11:55.549 --> 11:56.884
Yeah, what's going on?

11:58.719 --> 11:59.845
Why are you all dressed up?

11:59.845 --> 12:03.223
I made spinach lasagna.

12:03.223 --> 12:04.141
For lunch?

12:04.933 --> 12:06.101
What is happening?

12:06.101 --> 12:07.644
FRANKIE:
And there's an apple crisp

12:07.644 --> 12:09.354
and ice cream for dessert.

12:09.354 --> 12:11.398
Was this just some ploy
to get me to come home?

12:11.398 --> 12:12.691
Don't ask me.

12:12.691 --> 12:13.775
No, it wasn't a ploy.

12:13.775 --> 12:15.903
Okay, well, I had to call in sick.

12:15.903 --> 12:18.780
And I still didn't finish that essay
that's due Monday.

12:18.780 --> 12:21.617
I can't just come home
just because you miss me.

12:21.617 --> 12:22.618
No one misses you.

12:22.618 --> 12:24.870
Yeah? That's why
you keep begging me to come visit?

12:24.870 --> 12:26.872
[sighs] Sit down, everything's ready.

12:26.872 --> 12:29.416
CLARE: No, I'm not gonna sit down
until you tell me what was so important

12:29.416 --> 12:31.376
that I drop everything and come home.

12:36.298 --> 12:38.342
Well, it turns out that...

12:40.552 --> 12:44.306
this cold that I seem
to have had for months

12:44.806 --> 12:46.308
is, um...

12:47.935 --> 12:49.186
It isn't a cold.

12:50.187 --> 12:51.396
Okay. Well, what is it?

12:55.067 --> 12:57.069
♪ somber music playing ♪

12:59.738 --> 13:00.739
Mom?

13:09.414 --> 13:11.917
Honey, what are you doing?

13:11.917 --> 13:13.710
We're gonna need everything we have.

13:13.710 --> 13:14.586
Lucas, help me.

13:14.586 --> 13:16.255
- I don't think--
- Lucas, just help me!

13:18.423 --> 13:20.342
FRANKIE:
Well, will you at least have
something to eat?

13:21.093 --> 13:22.344
You still need to eat.

13:22.344 --> 13:23.178
Piles of four.

13:24.263 --> 13:25.472
We're gonna see every doctor we can.

13:26.306 --> 13:28.809
There's a cancer center in San Francisco,

13:28.809 --> 13:31.061
and we're going to get a second opinion

13:31.061 --> 13:33.355
and a third and fourth opinion.

13:33.355 --> 13:35.023
And I'm gonna call Jess.

13:35.649 --> 13:36.650
Jess' parents can help.

13:36.650 --> 13:39.069
I'm gonna call him tonight
so that-- so that he can call them.

13:39.069 --> 13:41.363
FRANKIE:
Honey, there are no more opinions to get.

13:42.030 --> 13:42.948
[softly] That's $5...

13:42.948 --> 13:46.076
The whole team of doctors
looked at the scan.

13:46.577 --> 13:50.497
- I have stage IV terminal lung cancer.
- Please stop.

13:50.497 --> 13:51.623
FRANKIE:
It's not treatable.

13:53.375 --> 13:54.918
We aren't going to treat it.

13:54.918 --> 13:56.336
Stop saying that!

13:56.336 --> 13:58.088
Jesus, Clare. You think that's helping?

14:01.592 --> 14:02.759
I was thinking...

14:04.178 --> 14:05.762
if you want to reach out to your dad...

14:05.762 --> 14:07.472
Why are you bringing him up?

14:07.472 --> 14:08.599
FRANKIE:
Because he's your father.

14:09.183 --> 14:10.809
And people can change.

14:11.560 --> 14:13.979
And it's okay to love him
even when I'm gone.

14:16.690 --> 14:17.941
CLARE:
Well, you're not gonna be gone.

14:21.445 --> 14:23.197
You two may have given up, but I haven't.

14:26.867 --> 14:28.076
[exhales] Okay.

14:37.419 --> 14:38.795
MAN:
Wait, I don't get it.

14:38.795 --> 14:40.797
- WOMAN 1:
- That's what the kids are into, James.

14:40.797 --> 14:43.091
You're watching
someone on the Internet eating?

14:43.091 --> 14:45.344
Oh, but have you seen
the girl that does her hair

14:45.344 --> 14:48.972
and tells you about women
who just <i>snap</i> and kill people?

14:48.972 --> 14:50.849
Oh, that's quality right there.

14:50.849 --> 14:53.769
Rae, grab your basket and come out here
and help your cousin find eggs.

14:53.769 --> 14:56.939
Some of those eggs, they got 20s in 'em.

14:56.939 --> 14:59.024
You know what I used to do for $20?

14:59.024 --> 15:00.317
No one knows.

15:00.317 --> 15:02.319
[all chuckling]

15:03.654 --> 15:06.573
♪

15:06.573 --> 15:07.991
Mommy!

15:11.537 --> 15:12.538
What're you doing here?

15:15.666 --> 15:16.667
CLARE:
Uh...

15:18.001 --> 15:20.546
I've-- I've brought pastries.

15:24.550 --> 15:26.552
Clare, can I get you something to eat?

15:26.552 --> 15:28.637
- Oh.
- I'm gonna fix you something to eat.

15:28.637 --> 15:31.932
Danny said you weren't coming
or I would've left lunch out.

15:31.932 --> 15:33.141
Oh, I never said I wasn't--

15:33.141 --> 15:36.270
Hey, Clare. No chicken salad today?

15:36.270 --> 15:37.688
Uh, I didn't have time to make chicken--

15:37.688 --> 15:39.857
I just can't with those raisins.

15:40.274 --> 15:42.860
They're currants.
I put currants in the chicken.

15:42.860 --> 15:43.861
Ignore her.

15:44.862 --> 15:47.531
Wouldn't be Easter without you, all right?

15:47.948 --> 15:50.409
And hey, don't worry about Rae.

15:50.409 --> 15:52.619
Danny ever come home on a surfboard?

15:53.370 --> 15:56.331
- I was talking about college.
- Hmm.

15:56.331 --> 15:58.625
If you all need help, we got you.

16:00.043 --> 16:03.463
WOMAN 2: Let me tell you,
if I gave away my kid's college fund,

16:03.463 --> 16:06.091
I'd be somewhere
way worse than in the basement, okay?

16:08.010 --> 16:09.678
WOMAN 1:
Here, Clare. Have something to eat.

16:10.262 --> 16:11.263
You want some ham?

16:12.181 --> 16:13.182
Okay.

16:14.183 --> 16:15.434
[softly] Are you fucking kidding me?

16:15.434 --> 16:16.643
[softly] It-- It-- It came up.

16:16.643 --> 16:18.228
What the fuck do you mean,
"It came up"?

16:18.228 --> 16:19.813
- Clare--
- 'Cause clearly you told them!

16:19.813 --> 16:23.400
Clare, you gave your brother
$15,000 of our money.

16:23.400 --> 16:25.861
It's a big fucking deal!
I told my dad. So what?

16:25.861 --> 16:30.616
You know how much of <i>our</i> money
we give to <i>your</i> family every fucking year?

16:30.616 --> 16:34.286
This whole city
is crawling with your relatives.
- Okay?

16:34.286 --> 16:38.540
There's graduation. There's weddings.
There's baby showers. There's holidays.

16:38.540 --> 16:41.251
All I'm doing is making chicken salad
that just goes wasted!

16:41.251 --> 16:42.503
Yeah, because no one likes raisins!

16:42.503 --> 16:43.921
They're currants!

16:43.921 --> 16:46.381
And they're fucking expensive,
so just add that to the tab!

16:46.381 --> 16:49.134
- Tab? So-- So we're keeping tally on--
- No, I'm just making a point!

16:49.134 --> 16:51.929
- You give me so much shit about Lucas...
- Yeah.

16:51.929 --> 16:53.805
...when all I do
is shit for <i>your</i> family!

16:53.805 --> 16:55.265
<i>Our</i> family, Clare.

16:55.849 --> 16:59.937
Okay, the same family that love us
and care for us and took you in.

16:59.937 --> 17:01.188
And-- And--

17:01.188 --> 17:02.105
You know what?
At the end of the day,

17:02.105 --> 17:03.982
it's not even just about the money.

17:06.109 --> 17:08.278
You gave that away
without even talking to me about it.

17:09.029 --> 17:11.782
- I'm your husband.
- So just take my side.

17:12.950 --> 17:14.117
Just be on my side.

17:16.328 --> 17:19.039
And stop
giving your aunt a fucking excuse

17:19.039 --> 17:22.543
to make that fucking face at me
every time she fucking sees me!

17:22.543 --> 17:23.544
[yelling] Enough!

17:27.673 --> 17:30.259
Oh. A-- A different aunt.

17:32.761 --> 17:34.972
Oh, my God, what is wrong with you?

17:34.972 --> 17:38.267
You can't keep trapping people
in tiny spaces just to yell at them!

17:38.267 --> 17:39.351
CLARE:
None of this is okay.

17:39.768 --> 17:40.769
Sneaking out.

17:41.395 --> 17:42.396
Getting drunk.

17:43.939 --> 17:45.691
Being so mean to me!

17:45.691 --> 17:47.943
Why are you so mean to me? Huh?

17:49.278 --> 17:51.321
- No--
- Just stop!

17:51.321 --> 17:53.073
Do you know what's going on out there?

17:53.073 --> 17:54.700
It is a war zone!

17:54.700 --> 17:57.286
There are condoms laced with fentanyl.

17:57.286 --> 17:58.412
You don't even know
what you're talking about.

17:58.412 --> 17:59.621
That's not a thing.

17:59.621 --> 18:02.666
All I'm saying
is that you need to be careful.

18:02.666 --> 18:04.293
You need to be smart.

18:04.293 --> 18:06.670
You need to find friends
who have your back.

18:06.670 --> 18:07.880
I have friends.

18:09.047 --> 18:10.340
What-- What about Bethany?

18:10.340 --> 18:12.301
- Bethany? Bethany?
- Yes. She was so sweet.

18:12.301 --> 18:14.928
You know Bethany had anal sex
on a Greyhound going to Reno?

18:14.928 --> 18:16.680
- What?
- Yeah.

18:16.680 --> 18:19.224
Why would she want
to take a bus to Reno?

18:19.224 --> 18:21.977
I don't know, maybe she was hoping
it would crash just to annoy her mother.

18:25.230 --> 18:26.523
Okay.

18:26.523 --> 18:27.983
I'ma pray for that Bethany.

18:27.983 --> 18:28.984
Thank you.

18:34.448 --> 18:35.449
Our father

18:36.325 --> 18:38.452
who art in heaven, hallowed be thy--

18:39.745 --> 18:40.746
Hallowed be thy--

18:52.591 --> 18:53.800
Fuck Fathers!

18:55.135 --> 18:57.596
Fuck you! Fuck you!

18:57.596 --> 18:59.515
MAN: Didn't you ever hear
you catch more flies

18:59.515 --> 19:00.682
with honey than vinegar?

19:01.767 --> 19:03.810
That's what your mama always says to me.

19:06.146 --> 19:07.147
She's gonna die.

19:11.235 --> 19:12.236
It's lung cancer.

19:13.570 --> 19:14.655
She just found out.

19:18.325 --> 19:19.326
Uh-- I'm s--

19:20.953 --> 19:21.954
I'm so sorry.

19:23.372 --> 19:24.373
That, uh...

19:28.001 --> 19:29.711
Oh, hon.

19:32.798 --> 19:33.799
[Clare crying]

19:34.716 --> 19:39.096
Anything I can do,
Liv and me, we're just up the road.

19:49.356 --> 19:50.357
Lady.

19:52.276 --> 19:53.277
Sell me Lady.

19:53.277 --> 19:54.486
Oh, darlin', she's--

19:54.486 --> 19:58.240
I've-- I've got, um...
I've got $386 right now.

19:58.866 --> 19:59.867
And after that, I can--

20:00.993 --> 20:02.536
I can give you monthly payments.

20:02.536 --> 20:05.080
And however much you need,
I'll pay it. I just, uh--

20:08.083 --> 20:09.501
A horse would save her life.

20:12.462 --> 20:15.340
And I-- I just-- I really--
I need to save her life.

20:15.340 --> 20:16.341
Clare.

20:18.468 --> 20:19.469
Go home.

20:20.512 --> 20:21.513
Be with your mom.

20:23.557 --> 20:24.850
I'll be praying for y'all.

20:26.393 --> 20:27.394
[scoffs]

20:36.320 --> 20:37.988
Oh, my God.

20:41.366 --> 20:42.367
[distant crying]

20:47.831 --> 20:49.833
[indistinct chatter]

20:52.920 --> 20:53.921
[crying continues]

21:03.180 --> 21:04.181
[crying continues]

21:05.599 --> 21:07.601
[woman crying]
[baby wailing]

21:17.236 --> 21:20.697
- [baby continues wailing]
- Shhh.

21:20.697 --> 21:21.698
I'm sorry.

21:22.824 --> 21:24.243
I didn't know what to write.

21:24.243 --> 21:25.827
I didn't have the words.

21:25.827 --> 21:26.828
WOMAN 1:
Clare?

21:28.080 --> 21:30.666
I'm glad you're here.
I was afraid you went home.

21:36.672 --> 21:38.715
- I--
- This isn't about the currants, is it?

21:39.216 --> 21:40.676
Oh, psh.

21:40.676 --> 21:42.803
I-- I'm just failing
at everything right now.

21:42.803 --> 21:43.804
I just feel like--

21:44.847 --> 21:45.848
Sorry.

21:46.348 --> 21:48.767
Danny and I are-- are fighting.

21:48.767 --> 21:49.935
I know you know that.

21:52.604 --> 21:56.108
And, uh, Frankie can't stand me.

21:56.525 --> 21:57.526
Rae.

21:57.526 --> 22:00.487
[exhales]
I have such a hard time calling her that.

22:03.198 --> 22:05.117
I just feel like
there's a wall between us.

22:05.701 --> 22:08.203
[crying] And I'm so afraid
that something bad is gonna happen.

22:09.746 --> 22:11.874
You're not gonna lose her.

22:11.874 --> 22:13.166
There was a reason...

22:14.585 --> 22:18.714
that I-- that I named her after my mom.

22:22.134 --> 22:25.596
Must be hard sometimes coming here.

22:25.596 --> 22:29.808
Oh, no! I'm just so grateful to you.

22:29.808 --> 22:32.060
For all of you. So grateful.

22:32.060 --> 22:33.478
It can be both.

22:37.024 --> 22:38.025
All that...

22:39.234 --> 22:43.363
strength and courage and love
you had to find inside yourself

22:43.363 --> 22:44.907
after your mom died,

22:44.907 --> 22:46.658
you poured right into Rae.

22:46.658 --> 22:48.702
You became the amazing mom you are

22:48.702 --> 22:53.081
because you were forced
to learn to mother yourself.

22:53.081 --> 22:54.416
I am not amazing.

22:55.083 --> 22:57.878
Here. I'm gonna do something.

22:57.878 --> 22:59.963
Oh, no, no. I'm-- I don't--
This is not my--

22:59.963 --> 23:01.840
Dear Heavenly Father.

23:01.840 --> 23:02.841
[Clare sighs]

23:02.841 --> 23:05.093
We come before you humbly,

23:05.802 --> 23:11.683
requesting that you look out
for our dear, sweet baby girl,

23:11.683 --> 23:12.935
Frankie Rae.

23:15.354 --> 23:19.525
And that we all accept
who she is telling us she wants to be.

23:20.317 --> 23:23.612
We ask that you wrap
your loving arms around...

23:24.655 --> 23:26.073
our precious Rae

23:27.699 --> 23:28.992
and Clare.

23:30.536 --> 23:32.663
Protect them from harm, Lord.

23:33.747 --> 23:35.082
And we pray...

23:35.916 --> 23:39.837
that Clare feels us, her family...

23:42.256 --> 23:46.718
<i>holding her in your divine love...</i>

23:50.472 --> 23:52.474
<i>just like you held her before.</i>

23:54.268 --> 23:57.688
[Frankie sobbing]

24:15.205 --> 24:16.206
YOUNG CLARE:
Mom.

24:20.460 --> 24:21.837
CLARE:
<i>Dear Terrified,</i>

24:24.965 --> 24:26.758
<i>I can't tell you how sorry I am</i>

24:26.758 --> 24:28.844
<i>for what you and your family
are going through.</i>

24:30.137 --> 24:31.138
I'm sorry.

24:32.097 --> 24:33.932
CLARE: <i>When I learned
my mom was gonna die of cancer,</i>

24:33.932 --> 24:35.684
<i>she was only 45.</i>

24:36.935 --> 24:38.604
<i>And I was terrified too.</i>

24:39.313 --> 24:40.564
<i>I was also angry.</i>

24:41.523 --> 24:43.692
<i>If God wasn't gonna save my mom,</i>

24:43.692 --> 24:46.403
<i>then I thought
God was either a ruthless bitch</i>

24:47.362 --> 24:49.907
<i>or more likely, just didn't exist.</i>

24:51.074 --> 24:52.159
<i>But if He does,</i>

24:52.159 --> 24:56.496
<i>I know He's not some spirit man
who may or may not hear our prayers</i>

24:56.496 --> 24:59.958
<i>and swoop in to save us
when the going gets rough.</i>

25:00.667 --> 25:03.504
- I mean, she could have texted.
- Yeah.

25:04.296 --> 25:08.467
<i>So what if
we thought about God differently?</i>

25:08.467 --> 25:11.512
- FRANKIE: Just call me, okay?
- Okay.

25:11.512 --> 25:15.015
CLARE: <i>And realize that
God isn't in the answers to our prayers,</i>

25:15.849 --> 25:18.685
<i>but in the people praying for us.</i>

25:18.685 --> 25:20.145
[horse whinnying]

25:21.980 --> 25:26.193
<i>What if, together,
those people form a raft?</i>

25:26.902 --> 25:28.111
Oh, my God.

25:29.029 --> 25:32.115
CLARE:
<i>That will hold your weight
and keep you afloat</i>

25:32.115 --> 25:35.744
<i>by the human love given to you
when you needed it the most.</i>

25:39.790 --> 25:42.209
She's yours
as long as you'd like to keep her.

25:45.337 --> 25:48.340
♪

25:55.389 --> 25:57.140
CLARE:
<i>If I believed in God,</i>

25:57.140 --> 25:59.518
<i>I'd see evidence of his existence in that.</i>

26:06.984 --> 26:09.987
♪

26:20.664 --> 26:21.915
<i>So, Terrified,</i>

26:24.585 --> 26:26.420
<i>what if you didn't worry
about everyone's God...</i>

26:26.420 --> 26:28.505
[Rae heaving]

26:28.505 --> 26:30.757
Okay, I got it. I got it.

26:31.925 --> 26:32.926
[Danny sighs]

26:32.926 --> 26:34.553
<i>...and allowed your God to exist</i>

26:34.553 --> 26:37.764
<i>in the simple words of compassion
others offer you?</i>

26:41.018 --> 26:42.936
She was the reason
I got up in the morning.

26:44.062 --> 26:45.147
Montana.

26:45.147 --> 26:47.191
CLARE:
<i>What if faith is the way it feels</i>

26:47.191 --> 26:50.027
<i>to lay your hand
on your daughter's sacred body,</i>

26:50.777 --> 26:53.780
<i>under the same big sky
where your mother held you?</i>

26:55.199 --> 26:56.783
<i>What if in your darkest hour,</i>

26:57.451 --> 27:00.621
<i>amidst your greatest fears
and your deepest losses,</i>

27:03.081 --> 27:04.875
<i>you saw the miracle in that?</i>

27:08.754 --> 27:11.256
[horse neighs]

27:13.258 --> 27:14.259
<i>Yours,</i>

27:16.345 --> 27:17.346
<i>Sugar.</i>

27:21.975 --> 27:25.979
<i>♪ I may not always love you ♪</i>

27:27.272 --> 27:31.443
<i>♪ But as long as
there are stars above you ♪</i>

27:32.694 --> 27:36.657
<i>♪ You'll never need to doubt it ♪</i>

27:37.699 --> 27:42.079
<i>♪ I'll make you so sure about it ♪</i>

27:43.413 --> 27:48.585
<i>♪ God only knows what I'd be without you ♪</i>

27:52.798 --> 27:55.801
♪

28:03.225 --> 28:06.520
<i>♪ Oh, God only knows ♪</i>

28:06.520 --> 28:10.190
<i>♪ What I'd be without you ♪</i>

28:12.734 --> 28:15.737
<i>♪ God only knows ♪</i>

28:15.737 --> 28:18.740
<i>♪ What I'd be ♪</i>

28:18.740 --> 28:24.496
<i>♪ Without you ♪</i>
